	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_MANXKERN">
			<Text>Kern</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIVILOPEDIA_UNITS_MANXKERN_TEXT">
			<Text>Gaelic warfare was for centuries centred around the Ceithearn (pronounced "Kern"), light skirmishing infantry who harried the enemy with missiles before charging. John Dymmok, serving under Elizabeth I's lord-lieutenant of Ireland, described the kerns as:[NEWLINE] [NEWLINE]"... A kind of footman, slightly armed with a sword, a target [round shield] of wood, or a bow and sheaf of arrows with barbed heads, or else three darts, which they cast with a wonderful facility and nearness..."[NEWLINE] [NEWLINE]en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gaelic_warfare</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_MANXKERN_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Kern (or Ceithearn) is a more powerful Pikeman. It has a ranged strike prior to melee combat and receives a bonus when fighting against mounted units, which makes it pretty much the only unit that can hope to stand up against a rampaging Knight. A Pikeman fortified in defensive terrain is a Knight's worst nightmare.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_HELP_MANXKERN">
			<Text>Specialized in defeating mounted Units; has a ranged attack prior to melee attack.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
  
